What you need to know:

Clinton Kibisu, a second year IT student, says the security system uses GSM technology, and guards against theft of livestock, farm produce, tools and equipment.The anti-theft system also has an added function - an outer door locking system that uses motors attached to the door, therefore if a thief manages to access a store at the farm, he cannot escape through the door. The system costs between Sh1,800 and Sh25,000. 